input.question: Among people with internet accounts containing "77" in the username, who has a pet named Elizabeth or Beth and works at a company where they are the only employee?

sql_queries.description: Find people with internet accounts containing '77' in the username
sql_queries.query: SELECT DISTINCT p.person_id, p.full_name FROM people p JOIN internet_accounts ia ON p.person_id = ia.owner_id WHERE ia.username LIKE '%77%'

sql_queries.description: Check which of these people have pets named Elizabeth or Beth
sql_queries.query: SELECT p.person_id, p.full_name, pt.name, pt.species FROM people p JOIN internet_accounts ia ON p.person_id = ia.owner_id JOIN pets pt ON p.person_id = pt.owner_id WHERE ia.username LIKE '%77%' AND (pt.name = 'Elizabeth' OR pt.name = 'Beth')

sql_queries.description: Check employment status for these people
sql_queries.query: SELECT DISTINCT p.person_id, p.full_name, e.company FROM people p JOIN internet_accounts ia ON p.person_id = ia.owner_id JOIN pets pt ON p.person_id = pt.owner_id JOIN employments e ON p.person_id = e.owner_id WHERE ia.username LIKE '%77%' AND (pt.name = 'Elizabeth' OR pt.name = 'Beth')

sql_queries.description: Verify which companies have only one employee
sql_queries.query: SELECT company, COUNT(*) as employee_count FROM employments WHERE company = 'Smith, Miller and Davis' GROUP BY company
